'''Salem Mohammed Shafi Al-Dawsari''' ({{langx|ar|سَالِم مُحَمَّد شَافِي الدَّوْسَرِيّ}}; born 19 August 1991) is a Saudi Arabian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a left winger and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] both [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]] and the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]].

==Early and personal life==
Al-Dawsari was born in [[Jeddah]] and joined [[Al Hilal SFC|Al Hilal]]'s youth academy at the age of 14.

==Club career==
Al-Dawsari made his debut for [[Al Hilal SFC|Al Hilal]] in 2010, at the age of 19. Apart from one year on loan at [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] as part of a deal between the [[Saudi Arabian Football Federation]] and [[La Liga]],<ref name=":0">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/may/30/salem-al-dawsari-saudi-arabia-winger-world-cup-villarreal |title=Salem al-Dawsari: the winger who represents a new breed of Saudi player |last=Wilcox |first=Gregory |date=30 May 2018 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=31 May 2018 |publisher=[[Guardian News and Media Limited]] |archive-date=18 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618051806/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/may/30/salem-al-dawsari-saudi-arabia-winger-world-cup-villarreal |url-status=live }}</ref> he has spent his entire career at Al Hilal.[[File:César Azpilicueta & Salem Al-Dawsari, Al Hilal SFC vs Chelsea F.C., 9 February 2022.jpg|thumb|Al-Dawsari (left) and [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]'s [[César Azpilicueta]] clashing during the [[2021 FIFA Club World Cup]]|left|237x237px]]

Al-Dawsari made one league appearance for Villarreal, coming on as a substitute against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] as the Yellow Submarine came from behind to draw 2–2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.villarrealusa.com/2022/11/27/23479469/where-villarreals-saudi-arabian-signings|title=Where are Villarreal’s two Saudi Arabian signings now?|work=Villarreal USA|date=27 November 2022|access-date=25 July 2024|author=Alayrach}}</ref>

In the second leg of the [[2019 AFC Champions League final]] on 24 November, Al-Dawsari scored the opening goal in an eventual 2–0 away win over [[Urawa Red Diamonds]], which saw Al-Hilal win the title following a 3–0 aggregate victory; the title allowed them to qualify for the [[2019 FIFA Club World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/clubworldcup/news/afc-champions-league-final-report |title=Al Hilal fire themselves to the Club World Cup |publisher=FIFA.com |date=24 November 2019 |access-date=24 November 2019 |archive-date=25 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191125005522/https://www.fifa.com/clubworldcup/news/afc-champions-league-final-report |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 7 February 2023, Al-Dawsari scored two [[Penalty (association football)|penalties]] against Brazilian club [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]] in the semi-finals of the [[2022 FIFA Club World Cup]]. Al Hilal won 3–2, becoming the first Saudi Arabian club to reach the final of the Club World Cup.<ref>{{cite news |title=Saudi Arabia's Al Hilal stun Flamengo to reach Club World Cup final |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/664847 |access-date=14 August 2024 |work=ESPN |agency=Reuters |date=8 February 2023 |language=en |archive-date=14 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240814120516/https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/664847 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 27 June 2025, Al-Dawsari scored in a 2–0 win over Mexican club [[C.F. Pachuca|Pachuca]] in the final group stage match of the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]], becoming the top Asian goalscorer in the history of the Club World Cup with 5 goals, surpassing [[Tsukasa Shiotani]] (4).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iffhs.com/posts/4454 |title=Club World Cup statistics (Group stage, 26–27 June) |publisher=[[IFFHS]] |date=27 June 2025 |accessdate=2 July 2025}}</ref> In October that year, he achieved his second [[Asian Footballer of the Year#AFC award|AFC Player of the Year]] award, becoming the first Saudi player to achieve this feat.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://saudigazette.com.sa/article/655815 |title=Salem Al Dawsari makes history with second AFC Player of the Year award in Riyadh |publisher=Saudi Gazette |date=17 October 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
Al-Dawsari was called up to the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]] for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC third round|2014 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]], and scored his first international goal in an away match against [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] in 2014<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-02-29/socceroos-bury-saudis-after-half-time/3861118 |title=Socceroos bury Saudis after half-time |date=29 February 2012 |work=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |access-date=31 May 2018 |publisher=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |archive-date=29 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129104014/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-02-29/socceroos-bury-saudis-after-half-time/3861118 |url-status=live }}</ref> In May 2018, he was named in Saudi Arabia's preliminary [[Saudi Arabia national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44083365 |title=World Cup 2018: All the confirmed squads for this summer's finals in Russia |date=18 May 2018 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |access-date=31 May 2018 |publisher=[[BBC]] |archive-date=18 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210418134149/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44083365 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 25 June, Al-Dawsari scored a late winning goal as his side won 2–1 over [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]] in their last group stage match of the World Cup.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jun/25/saudi-arabia-egypt-world-cup-2018-group-a-match-report|title=Salem al-Dawsari snatches win for Saudi Arabia against Egypt|work=The Guardian|date=25 June 2018|access-date=25 June 2018|archive-date=30 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190630051622/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jun/25/saudi-arabia-egypt-world-cup-2018-group-a-match-report|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 22 November 2022, Al-Dawsari scored his second goal at a [[FIFA World Cup]], his first at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022 edition]] in Qatar in a match against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]]. He made a run around the box before finishing past [[Emiliano Martínez]] to put Saudi Arabia ahead by a score of 2–1, which ended in a remarkable and historic victory for the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]].<ref>{{cite web |date=22 November 2022 |title=Argentina 1–2 Saudi Arabia: Salem Al-Dawsari scores stunner as pre-tournament favourites are shocked |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/world-cup/2022/fifa-world-cup-2022-in-qatar-live-argentina-v-saudi-arabia-updates_sto9237905/story.shtml |access-date=22 November 2022 |website=Eurosport |archive-date=22 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221122154214/https://www.eurosport.com/football/world-cup/2022/fifa-world-cup-2022-in-qatar-live-argentina-v-saudi-arabia-updates_sto9237905/story.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> On 30 November, Al-Dawsari scored a goal against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]], in which he equalled the record of most goals scored by a Saudi player in World Cups, three goals by [[Sami Al-Jaber]], as Saudi Arabia exited the World Cup with a 2–1 loss to Mexico.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thenationalnews.com/fifa-world-cup-2022/2022/11/30/mexico-end-saudi-arabias-world-cup-dream-but-still-exit-tournament/ |title=Mexico end Saudi Arabia's World Cup dream but still exit tournament |website=The National News |date=30 November 2022 |access-date=30 November 2022 |archive-date=30 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221130230812/https://www.thenationalnews.com/fifa-world-cup-2022/2022/11/30/mexico-end-saudi-arabias-world-cup-dream-but-still-exit-tournament/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 8 October 2025, he made his 100th international appearance in a 3–2 win over [[Indonesia national football team|Indonesia]] during the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC fourth round|2026 World Cup qualification fourth round]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/saudi-star-sets-record-al-dawsari-becomes-saudi-arabias-two-time-afc-player-of-the-year/articleshow/124626001.cms |title=Saudi star sets record: Al Dawsari becomes Saudi Arabia’s first two-time AFC player of the year |publisher=The Times of India |date=19 October 2025 }}</ref>

